<font color="#FF0000">GUILT AND &quot;AMNESTY&quot;</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 13 21:24:33 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art, <br>
You're right, we were betrayed when insult was added to our injuries because of the &quot;amnesty&quot; program. When I ran for Congress several years ago, I would have been going up against one of the authors of that program, but came in third in the primary.  I had visited his office in Washington and was discussed with the left wing communist paraphernalia he had on displayed in his office. The Soviet Union and communist China for his great humanitarian efforts had given many plagues to him. When I mentioned this in a campaign speech they were taken down from his office the following day. He's still in office, perhaps if I wasn't so busy writing here I would run again. Many believe that if I ever got through the primary, I would take that seat. Then as a Congressmen I could declare war on other nations, like Tennessee. <br><br>
  <br><br>
Tom, <br>
I never compared the Vietnam war with the war God instituted against the Midianites, I compared the lives of those that feared and trembled because of war with those who feared and trembled about going to war in Vietnam. There's a lot of difference. I've done the same with the stories I have posted, used them as examples of where the conversation had taken us. Compared then and now.<br>
I don't know if God sanctioned the war in Nam. <br>
I do know that there is a lot of similarities between the Midians and the Hanoi government who like them came against others to destroy their produce and spoil their land. But, if you have first hand knowledge that God did not institute the war in Nam then I guess I'll have to believe you. I've often wondered who's side was God on? <br>
I mean, the same Quakers that cared for the lame, often fed and cared for the communist soldiers I was there to kill. The Quakers provided them with not only American made  goods, food and stuff but also with medical supplies and assistance. <br>
There are only a few things that continue to bother me, I have compiled a series of stories regarding Divine Intervention in the Jungles of Vietnam (Oh! No, Not another Book) and I would post some of those stories here but I guess you would just scroll down, so I won't. <br><br>
I do know that I should have been killed several times in the rice paddies, jungles and on the many patrols I went on, but was not. Why I was spared, certainly not to post notes on this site, but then again maybe so. I can only thank God, I survived. <br>
I know I have accomplished much since that time, my life has not been idle, this morning I spent a greater part of my day, counseling a young couple preparing for marriage. I know their lives were transformed and that they will never be the same. Why, was I spared when I should have been killed, why did I survive in the midst of utter chaos, perhaps it was all just for that young couple. <br><br>
I have not changed my opinion about those that gave their WINTER SOLDIER TESTIMONY, I continue to believe they were deceived by a whole lot of communist propaganda, misinformation or as we used to call it disinformation. <br>
I only added guilt to their reasons. I have not changed my opinion about all those bias, slanted and worthless piece of mumbo jumbo, given and received by individuals sitting in judgement who had their own left wing agendas. I would have questioned the motives and the false perceptions that many of those individuals shared in the giving of their testimony. <br>
As I've said, I went to Nam to kill gooks. That's what I did, I killed Communist gooks, if others did wrong then they did so because of their own lack of self restrain but it was not our policy to kill innocent women and children as some of those testimonies would lead you to believe. <br><br>
In the Marine Corps they told us why we were going. What we were doing there and why. I believed them then and believe what I did was right. When a Marine did wrong he was removed from the field and as far as I know is still serving time. <br>
You're right that God didn't abandon Gideon, while our politicians abandoned us, but God had given the people of Israel over to be ruled by the Midians because they had not done what was right in His eyes. Perhaps that's why we lost the war. We had promised the South Vietnamese people we would help them fight communist aggression, but we abandoned them, we did not do what was right. Instead we brought shame into our homes by embracing and forgiving the cowards that ran to Canada and showered others that protested against the war with honor.<br><br>
Johnson I know was gutless and he abandoned us but that did not mean the war we were fighting was wrong. It became a dirty war because we did not have the guts to keep our word. To continue to fight for what was right. The price was too high a price to pay and we decided to stop fighting. The truth was that Johnson feared retaliation from China and the Soviet Union and escalation might lead to a nuclear war.  So, Johnson figured the Vietnamese people were not worth it. That's what it all came down to, those little gooks across the sea were not worth it. But I went there to fight for them, Gee, I volunteered to do so, but It's wrong for me to call them gooks and I am corrected by those that were drafted and who didn't want to go and by those that were not willing to fight for the little gooks right to live and enjoy our form of liberty. <br>

